Tekton
│
├─ 1. Overview
│   ├─ Kubernetes-native CI/CD
│   ├─ Declarative pipelines as Kubernetes CRDs
│   ├─ Cloud-agnostic
│   └─ Integrates with GitOps and existing CI/CD tools
│
├─ 2. Core Concepts
│   ├─ Task
│   │   ├─ Smallest unit of work
│   │   ├─ Containerized steps
│   │   └─ Defined as Tekton CRD
│   ├─ Pipeline
│   │   ├─ Sequence of Tasks
│   │   └─ Defines dependencies and order
│   ├─ PipelineRun
│   │   └─ Executes a Pipeline
│   ├─ TaskRun
│   │   └─ Executes a Task
│   ├─ PipelineResource (deprecated in Tekton 0.21+)
│   │   ├─ Git, Image, Storage, Cluster resources
│   │   └─ Used as inputs/outputs for Tasks
│   ├─ Params
│   │   └─ Parameterize Pipelines or Tasks
│   ├─ Workspaces
│   │   └─ Shared storage between Tasks
│   └─ Results
│       └─ Output values from Tasks
│
├─ 3. Triggers
│   ├─ Event-driven execution
│   ├─ Tekton Trigger CRDs
│   │   ├─ TriggerTemplate: template for PipelineRun/TaskRun
│   │   ├─ TriggerBinding: maps event payload to params
│   │   └─ EventListener: webhook endpoint to listen to events
│   └─ Integrations
│       ├─ GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket webhooks
│       └─ Cloud events
│
├─ 4. Observability & Logging
│   ├─ Pod logs for Task/Step execution
│   ├─ Tekton Dashboard
│   │   └─ Visualize Pipelines, Tasks, and Runs
│   ├─ Metrics
│   │   ├─ Prometheus metrics
│   │   └─ Track success/failure, duration, latency
│   └─ Tracing
│       └─ OpenTelemetry integration possible
│
├─ 5. Common Tools & Integrations
│   ├─ Tekton CLI (tkn)
│   ├─ Tekton Dashboard
│   ├─ GitHub Actions / GitLab CI integration
│   ├─ ArgoCD / Flux (GitOps integration)
│   └─ Artifact storage
│       ├─ OCI images (Harbor, DockerHub)
│       └─ MinIO / S3 for build artifacts
│
├─ 6. Security
│   ├─ RBAC for Pipeline/Task execution
│   ├─ ServiceAccounts for task Pods
│   └─ Secret management
│       └─ Kubernetes Secrets / Vault integration
│
├─ 7. Best Practices
│   ├─ Keep Tasks small and reusable
│   ├─ Parameterize Pipelines for flexibility
│   ├─ Version control for Pipeline CRDs
│   ├─ Use Workspaces for persistent storage
│   ├─ Monitor metrics and logs for reliability
│   └─ Integrate with GitOps for automated deployments
